content.description: Start with right hand on a side pull and left hand on an undercling. Go up and right.
content.location: To the left of "Tender Biddles V3"

content.description: Start with your left on a good sidepull/undercling crimp and your right somewhere in the crack, then go up and left through big moves to a dirty beached whale topout
content.location: On the downhill side of the furthest downhill boulder in the Upper Biddles

content.description: Start on the right-hand sidepull jug and traverse up and right along crimpy rails to a hueco just before topping out on a ledge.
content.location: On the uphill side of Upper Biddles rock near the start of Biddles Traverse.

content.description: Same start holds as The Thing. Two moves: Jump to the jug, jump to the top hold, finish as you would The Thing. If you start with left hand in the crack and right hand on a pinch, you can finish out right and that goes at V4, Flap Your Wings
content.location: Undercling in the middle of the cave part for left, somewhere in crack for right.

content.description: Same start as The Thing, jump to the jug, traverse out right around the bulge, top out.
content.location: same start holds as The Thing

content.description: Stand start and climb the technical/ insecure chimney over the tree. Flexibility helps.
content.protection: Pads or just dial it in.
content.location: On the backside of the boulder in front of a tree.

content.description: Start on a side pull, or farther right, and traverse to and up the chimney!
content.protection: A couple pads for the finish
content.location: Around the corner from the chimney.

content.description: Exciting highball with fragile crimps and a mega jug topout. Really only gets and R waiting if you're not solid at the grade and the extra fragile rock. Has potential to be much harder/ impossible after some idiot breaks the holds from climbing too soon after rain!!
content.location: Look for a rock with thin crimps and a mossy top out out with several huecos.
